# Sync Docker dev after changes

When changing `@shamar/*` packages (core, adonis, rest, lucid, mongoose, cherubim) or playground code that depends on rebuilt `dist`:

1. **Build** affected packages on the host so mounted `packages/*/dist` updates, e.g.:
   `pnpm --filter @shamar/core --filter @shamar/adonis --filter @shamar/rest build`
2. **Restart** the dev container so Adonis reloads providers/dist (HMR alone is not enough for `dist`/provider changes):
   `docker compose --profile dev restart app-dev`
3. **Verify** logs show the HTTP server started (`started HTTP server on 0.0.0.0:3333`).

Do this at the end of implementation work without waiting to be asked. Pure Edge/`assets`/`start` edits that are volume-mounted may only need HMR; still restart if the app looks stale or errors persist.
